},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining Native errors and tests**\\n\\nI'm considering whether catching the Native error could allow the test to pass without needing XMLBeans metadata. If the test catches it, the dynamic call sites could still reach the failure point. The native failure occurred at Constructor.newInstance within TypeSystemHolder.loadTypeSystem, which hit all three active call sites. If I catch `ExceptionInInitializerError`, then the test could pass. However, the instructions state that missing metadata tests need to run under Native. That's a bit confusing—if it's caught, does it still run and verify?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting agent configurations**\\n\\nI think I need to check if the user-code-filter can include `org.apache.xmlbeans` for generating metadata. It seems important to ensure that the generated agent configurations are set up correctly. I want to explore the `build/native/agent-output` to see what's being generated. It might help clarify whether adjustments are necessary for optimal performance. Let’s dig into that!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JjBmZP16ahEHi0B5pJ4OQ7nu|fc_00a513299eb38b1a0169ff82f5e7348194821d1d95e5370249", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.apache.poi/poi-ooxml-schemas/4.1.2/build -path '*native-image*' -type f | head -100 && find tests/src/org.apache.poi/poi-ooxml-schemas/4.1.2/build -type f -name 'reflect-config.json' -o -name 'resource-config.json' | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1419, "output": 1359, "cacheRead": 86528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 89306, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778352865353, "responseId": "resp_00a513299eb38b1a0169ff82e286b48194a89f8b593581468e"}}
